The Young Medical Laboratory Scientists Forum (YMLSF), has committed to making its human resource available for testing to fight the COVID19 pandemic in the country. YMLSF is a body of young medical laboratory scientists in Nigeria with over 30,000 members across the country. President of the Forum, MLS Isomah Chiladi, in a statement, decried a statement he said was credited to the Speaker of the House of Representatives, Femi Gbajabiamila, claiming that there are only two medical lab scientist experts in molecular testing in the country. He noted that the source of the statistic was not only wrong but also adversely deleterious to the medical laboratory human resource management, which according to him, is very cardinal at precarious times like this. “With the plethora of challenges in containing COVID-19 in Nigeria, it should interest you to know that diagnostic man power is completely out of this bracket as there are more  adequately trained medical laboratory scientists who are resource persons in molecular testing as evidenced in the compiled list of Nigerian experts sent to NCDC by Association of Medical Laboratory Scientists of Nigeria(AMLSN). “A tour to assess the level of preparedness from the medical laboratory experts would have been more appropriate by the house but considering the pandemic and complete lockdown by federal government, it will be our opinion that you kindly verify the facts from the appropriate authority/regulatory body (medical laboratory science council of Nigeria) established by the Act of the honorable chambers. “Laboratory Management as enshrined in our curriculum entails setting up any sort of medical or molecular laboratory, managing the laboratory and production of reliable and quality results for patient management and this we shall uphold to the people of Nigeria, ” Chiladi explained. The Association commended all the medical and health professionals, especially all medical laboratory scientists who are in front line in the fight against COVID 19. 